{:spec/title "Update workflow validator for pipeline format"
 :spec/description "Update workflow validator to support new :workflow/pipeline format instead of old :workflow/phases format.

Current problem:
- Validator (components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/validator.clj) requires :workflow/phases
- New workflows use :workflow/pipeline format
- This blocks loading modern workflows like simple-v2.0.0.edn

Required changes:
1. Accept :workflow/pipeline as valid alternative to :workflow/phases
2. Validate pipeline entries have :phase keyword
3. Remove requirement for :workflow/entry-phase (infer from first pipeline entry)
4. Update validation error messages to mention both formats
5. Ensure backward compatibility - both formats should work

Test workflows:
- simple-v2.0.0.edn (new format) should validate
- simple-test-v1.0.0.edn (old format) should still validate

Reference spec: specs/normative/N2-workflows.md"

 :spec/intent {:type :feature
          :scope ["components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/validator.clj"
                  "components/workflow/test/ai/miniforge/workflow/validator_test.clj"]}

 :spec/constraints ["maintain-backward-compatibility"
               "validate-both-formats"
               "include-tests"
               "follow-existing-validation-pattern"]

 :tags [:workflow :validation :migration :task-3]

 :context "Part of interceptor-based workflow migration. This is blocking the other migration tasks - must complete first."}
